npm i -g typescript
i = install
g = global in all folders typescript can be executed.

tsc -v
typescript compiler version.

///////////////////////////////
///////////////////////////////
Creating a tsc config file because by default, tsc is compiling ts to ES5 flavour of JS.
let a:number = 25; is giving: var a = 25;
But we should not use var much.

PS D:\Yashwanth\HTW_Berlin\Self_Learnings\Typescript>
PS D:\Yashwanth\HTW_Berlin\Self_Learnings\Typescript>
PS D:\Yashwanth\HTW_Berlin\Self_Learnings\Typescript> tsc --init

Created a new tsconfig.json with:  
 TS
target: es2016
module: commonjs
strict: true
esModuleInterop: true
skipLibCheck: true
forceConsistentCasingInFileNames: true

You can learn more at https://aka.ms/tsconfig
PS D:\Yashwanth\HTW_Berlin\Self_Learnings\Typescript>

/////////////
////////////
////////////

After I made the changes in tsconfig.json,
I can just run tsc on the cmd window. And it will generate the compiled files in dist folder
or distributable folder.
